"```sql\nSELECT (COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE income.amount = 50) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS percentage\nFROM member\nJOIN income ON member.member_id = income.link_to_member\nWHERE member.t_shirt_size = 'Medium' AND member.position = 'Member';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of income records with an amount of 50 received by members who have a t-shirt size of Medium and hold the position of Member. It uses a join between the `member` and `income` tables based on the foreign key relationship, and applies the conditions specified in the question and evidence."